cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on the analysis of social media accounts and their reactions to news sources, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to label responses, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the spread of misinformation and the role of bots, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper analyzes the behavior of human and bot accounts, which could fall under the category of social computing (cs.SOC).
